{
  "texts": [
    "At this level, learner modeling could also extend to include cognitive, emotional, affective, and motivational aspects.",
    "Currently, ChatGPT lacks the ability to create persistent and evolving models of individual learners that extend beyond a single session (Nazir & Wang, 2023).",
    "It does not possess long-term memory or the capability to track progress over time, both of which are essential for accurately modeling a learner's development.",
    "Higher levels of PL will also comprise adapting and selecting learning or pedagogical approaches, as different learners may require different learning or pedagogical approaches depending on their ZPD (Rakhmonov & Kurbonova, 2023).",
    "A system that can choose the appropriate learning approach would be able to adapt its teaching methods to best fit the learner's current abilities and preferred learning style, effectively facilitating movement through the ZPD (Wang, 2024)."
  ]
}